<br>
As you start out as a MT, you will be competing with Rogues, Monks, and melees weilding Windblades, etc. At some point your Wavecrasher/Frostbringer will need to be upgraded.<br>
<br>
Much later on you will see SEWS and BBB rather reqularly awarded to Knights. Obviously you will require a pretty darned good weapon to hold taunt.<br>
<br>
It occurs to me that this phenomena applies thoughout a Warrior's career and it suggests that there are &quot;tiers&quot; for aggro weapons.<br>
<br>
This works out something like:<br>
<br>
1. Wavecrasher/Frostbringer - Old World and Kunark; purchasable.<br>
<br>
2. Willsapper/Blade of Strategy - all pre-SoL excluding AoW, etc.<br>
<br>
3. Cord Hilted SpikeDriver/Blade of Carnage - all, excluding big damage reposting or Damage Shielded mobs.<br>
<br>
4. Blade of War or Obsidean Greatblade - all, particularly big damage reposting or Damage Shielded mobs<br>
<br>
Obviously other weapons can be substituted for these and the boundries aren't absolutely fixed. But, In my experiance this is in fact pretty much how the type of mobs your guild is taking on and the quality of aggro weapons needed by MT's is related.<br>
